Irion County High School
August 19 at 7:51 PM ·

Good afternoon,

We are so excited about school starting tomorrow. Please remember that our health and safety depends on families and parents being honest and keeping their kiddos home if they have fever or are sick. Also, you are required to report to the school if your student has Covid 19. There is a list of three requirements that will allow your child to come back to school. For detailed information, review our reopening plan on the district website. We want to be able to stay in school, and you can help us make that happen!

See you tomorrow!

It is with great sadness that we report that the UIL has officially canceled all remaining events for the 2019-2020 school year. We understand the difficulty involved in making this decision and the importance of maintaining social distancing to limit contact with others. We support that decision and will continue to do our part in stopping the spread of the COVID-19 here in Texas.

With that said, the ICISD coaching staff wants our athletes to know, especially our seniors, that we are heartbroken for them. We were so excited and had such high expectations for this spring.

Seniors, thank you for your dedication over the years. We are thinking of you during this time.

#weareIC

post_text:
IC Hornets:

We found several workout cards for you to choose from to get workouts in at home - some harder than others (you can find more on the internet). The truth is with these works as with any workout, you only get out of it what you put into it! If you want to add weights to some of the movements you can fill milk jugs with water, use old tires, cases of bottled water, etc. Be creative and be sure to share your ideas with others (if they work 🤣)!

Since we can't have practices, find ways to work on your skills by yourself or with your immediate family. You can always find places to run - so do conditioning workouts like we always do. Modified running (12 sec jog, 8 sec sprint), build-ups, ladders, plyo's, etc. Hit golf balls in your yard, play catch with siblings or parents, play tennis somewhere with your own equipment and with family, play basketball, etc., all while following government/UIL guidelines and recommendations 😬.

Let us know if you need anything out of the locker room and we will get it for you.

- IC Coaching Staff

#keepactive #daybyday #HornetPride

post_text:
Playing with only 5 girls for the tournament, the JVG's won the Consolation bracket today beating Early and San Angelo Central!
All-Tournament - Maci Sparks

Also playing with only 5, the freshmen girls finished 5th overall in the JVG's tournament!
All-Tournament - Audrey Tillman & Kaylee Walston

And with only 6 girls, the Varsity went 2-2 in their pool, losing to Christoval and Abilene Cooper, defeating Harper and Iraan.
All-Tournament - Mercedes Davis

We are very proud of their fight over the weekend and saw a lot of growth with each game. We are happy with where we are right now and ready to start district on Tuesday at home against Bronte!

#goLadyHornets
#weareIC
#stingem

post_text: We are doing a football playoff shirt order today and today only. We will not have an order form to send home with kids due to time restraints. Anyone wanting shirts needs to send size information to tconner@irion-isd.org or text her with your name and sizes to (806) 470-2840. The shirts will be light grey with purple and white print and include a roster on the back. Price estimates are $15 for short sleeve and around $18 for long sleeve. All we need at this time is your sizes and we will collect money later this week when we deliver them. Please share this information with others. Thanks and GO HORNETS!!!

I forgot to mention that you can always help out by volunteering with the Booster Club (contact Bill Taylor), helping with game day travel goodie bags, or volunteering to help when IC hosts an event (contact the coaching staff) !

Don't forgot that we will size football helmets/shoulder pads tomorrow - HS from 1:00-3:00, JH 3:00-4:00!
